Add Channel-Object Linking Rules for Voice Calls (Beta)

Create object-linking rules for incoming customer voice calls. When an agent accepts a call in the workspace, prompt them to choose from recommended contact records, search for a record, or add a new one.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience with the Digital Engagement add-on SKU.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud.

Setup Steps:
Set up Voice before creating your channel-object linking rules.
In Service Setup, create a rule name and description. Set actions for scenarios where no record is found or one matching record is found.
Save your work.

For example, if no matches are found, you can include a rule to automatically create and link a record. Or prompt the agent to search for a record or create a record. If only one matching record is found, set a rule to automatically link the record, or show a prompt asking the agent to pick the suggested record.

After completing the Phone setup, add Object-Linking Notifications background utility in Lightning App Builder to show prompts as toast messages in the Service Console.
